//@version=6
indicator("UDB-ORB TSLA A - Peak-Trail (Config A)", shorttitle="UDB-ORB A", overlay=true, max_labels_count=500)

//=============================================================================================
//  UDB-ORB TSLA v2.0  —  Pine port of the Python engine's CURRENT DEFAULT config
//  Source of truth: github.com/Thiyagarajan1978/udb-orb-tsla   (config/config.yaml)
//=============================================================================================
//
//  WHY THIS DIFFERS FROM "UDB v12.4.3 / Adaptive TP + Reversal"
//  ------------------------------------------------------------
//  The old script filled stop exits AT the stop level, as if a resting stop order existed.
//  This is an ALERTS-ONLY system: the signal fires on the 5-minute BAR CLOSE, so you act after
//  the candle closes and fill at/around that close. Fixing that one thing cut the 6-month P&L
//  from +$522 to +$214. Everything below was then RE-TUNED under realistic fills.
//
//   1. RESTING STOP (the big one)  : ADOPTED 2026-07-11. Stop exits (BE Stop / BE Trail / Base SL
//                                    / runner-trail) fill INTRABAR at the level, gap-aware — a REAL
//                                    broker OCO stop, so a BE stop fills at ~entry (not a bar close
//                                    far below). +18% net & half the worst day vs the old close-fill
//                                    model. Set "Stop exits fill at bar CLOSE" ON to see the old
//                                    alerts-only numbers. (You must PLACE resting stops to get this.)
//   2. VOLATILITY REGIME GATE (NEW): skip the day when prior-20d realised daily vol > 4.92%.
//                                    This is a LOW-VOL breakout system — a high-vol bar closes
//                                    further past the stop, so BE-stop cost scales with vol.
//                                    The top vol quintile is the ONLY net-negative bucket.
//   3. BE trigger 0.35 -> 0.55     : fewer premature BE stops.
//   4. Reversal capture            : enter the reversal on a RAW opposite OR break (earlier) and
//                                    let it TRAIL TO EOD (no fixed $5 TP, no partial).
//   5. Runner exit (75%)           : PEAK-TRAIL (Config A default): trails 0.75 x OR below the peak.
//                                    OR toggle "Runner Exit (75%)" -> VWAP CROSS (Config B): ride
//                                    until close crosses back thru session VWAP. VWAP made more net
//                                    3yr (+574 vs +469/unit) but bumpier -> A/B test it live.
//   6. Max OR width $8             : skip wide-OR whipsaw days.
//   7. Reversal RISK PARITY (NEW)  : the 2x size was never risk-adjusted. The reversal enters
//                                    after price crossed the whole OR, so its stop is far away;
//                                    at 2x it carried 1.6x the primary's risk and caused 68% of
//                                    worst-day damage. Its qty is now scaled so its DOLLAR RISK
//                                    <= $6 (the primary's average risk).
//   8. Slippage $0.02 / unit charged on every exit leg.
//   9. CONFIRMATION CANDLE (now OFF): a 2-candle-hold entry filter. Adopted under close-fill for
//                                    win rate, but net-NEGATIVE under the resting stop (which
//                                    already caps whipsaws at $5) -> turned OFF (Config A, §24;
//                                    +298 -> +469/unit, better all 3 yrs). ON only with close-fill.
//  10. MAX-CAP $5 STOP             : the primary stop is capped at $5 from entry (also bounds the
//                                    entry->stop distance). Cuts the 2024
//                                    worst day (-14.9 -> -8.7) that the later entry would create.
//                                    (These two are a package: the cap earns its place only with
//                                    confirmation — standalone it was noise.)
//
//  PYTHON-VALIDATED RESULTS — DEFAULT NOW = 2-candle confirmation + Max-Cap $5 stop
//  (TSLA 5m, realistic fills, 1 unit, slippage $0.02)
//  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  DEFAULT "Config A" = RESTING STOP (touch) + $0.10 slippage + CONFIRMATION OFF.
//     Year        Trades   WR      Net        PF     Worst day   Reversals
//     2024         251    45.0%   + $137.9    1.58   -$7.90         63
//     2025         236    47.0%   + $103.7    1.32   -$8.85         51
//     2026 (H1)    151    53.6%   + $227.8    2.46   -$6.90         29
//     2024-26 H1   638    47.8%   + $469.4    1.65   -$8.85        143   (full ledger)
//     Confirmation now OFF: net-negative under the resting stop (+298 -> +469, +57%; see §24).
//
//  To reproduce the OLD immediate-entry numbers: turn OFF "Require confirmation candle" and set
//  "Max Stop Distance from Entry" to 0 (2024 253tr/45.1%/+65.67, 2025 236tr/47.5%/+82.71).
//  NOTE: 2026 was a LOW-VOLATILITY regime — that is WHY it outperformed. Size off 2024.
//  The original script's advertised +$5,528 was a fill-model artifact; under realistic fills
//  that same config LOSES money in 2024 (-$70, PF 0.85).
//
//  BUFFER = 10%. 14% was swept across all 3 years and rejected: the curve is noise (2024 jumps
//  ~$10 between adjacent settings), worst day is IDENTICAL at every buffer, and 14%'s only edge
//  comes from 2026 — the friendly regime. In 2024 (the year you size off) 10% is better.
//  ==> If your chart shows Long Trigger 396.19 on 2026-07-09, your buffer is 14%. Set it to 10%
//      (10% gives 396.01) or nothing will reconcile against the Python engine.
//
//  READING THE REVERSAL (e.g. 2026-07-09)
//  --------------------------------------
//  The reversal is ALWAYS the OPPOSITE direction of the primary, and the primary stopping only
//  ARMS it — it fires only when price CLOSES beyond the RAW opposite OR boundary. That level is
//  now plotted (purple circles) whenever a reversal is armed, so you can see exactly what price
//  had to do. On 2026-07-09 the primary was LONG, so the reversal could only be a SHORT needing
//  a close < 390.86; the lowest close after the stop was 392.98 and the day rallied to 406.55.
//  Forcing that short at its best price would have LOST -$3.12. Not firing was correct.
//
//  APPLY TO: TSLA, 5-minute chart, Regular Trading Hours.
//  The table's Net P&L is per 1 unit and should track the Python engine closely. Small
//  divergences are expected from TradingView's data feed vs FMP, and from Pine's daily-bar
//  close used for the volatility gate.
//=============================================================================================

// ==================== INPUTS ====================
grpS = "Session"
eodHour = input.int(15, "EOD Exit Hour", minval=0, maxval=23, group=grpS)
eodMin  = input.int(50, "EOD Exit Minute", minval=0, maxval=59, group=grpS)

grpR = "Risk / Regime Gates"
maxORWidth  = input.float(8.0,  "Max OR Width ($) — skip wider days", step=0.5, group=grpR)
volLookback = input.int(20,     "Volatility Lookback (days)", minval=2, group=grpR)
maxRvolPct  = input.float(4.92, "Max Prior Realised Daily Vol (%)", step=0.01, group=grpR, tooltip="Skip the day when the prior N-day stdev of daily returns exceeds this. Threshold fitted on 2024-25 ONLY; 2026 was out-of-sample and has ~no such days.")

grpE = "Entry"
bufferPctOR = input.float(10.0, "Breakout Buffer (% of OR width)", step=0.5, group=grpE)
tradeQty    = input.float(1.0,  "Units Per Trade", minval=0.01, group=grpE)
slippage    = input.float(0.10, "Slippage Per Unit (charged on each exit)", step=0.01, group=grpE, tooltip="0.10 = conservative allowance for stop-fill slippage / liquidity sweeps (a resting stop becomes a market order and can fill worse than the level). Was 0.02.")

grpX = "Exits (tuned under realistic fills)"
adaptiveTPScale = input.float(1.0,  "Adaptive TP — OR Width Multiplier", step=0.05, group=grpX)
adaptiveTPMin   = input.float(2.14, "Adaptive TP — Minimum Floor ($)", step=0.01, group=grpX)
beTrigger       = input.float(0.55, "BE Retrace Trigger (% of OR width)", step=0.05, group=grpX)
maxCapSL        = input.float(5.0,  "Max Stop Distance from Entry ($, 0=off)", step=0.5, group=grpX, tooltip="Caps the OR-boundary primary stop so it is never further than this from entry. Pairs with the confirmation candle (which enters later/more extended). 0 = plain OR-boundary stop.")
beTrailAmt      = input.float(0.25, "BE Trail Amount ($)", step=0.01, group=grpX)
partialPct      = input.float(25.0, "Partial Exit Quantity (%)", step=1.0, group=grpX)
runnerMult      = input.float(0.75, "Runner Peak-Trail (x OR width)", step=0.05, group=grpX)
runnerExit      = input.string("Peak Trail", "Runner Exit (75%)", options=["Peak Trail", "VWAP Cross"], group=grpX, tooltip="Peak Trail = Config A (DEFAULT): the 75% runner trails runnerMult x OR below its peak. VWAP Cross = Config B: the runner rides until price CLOSES back through the session VWAP (after +$ arm-profit). Backtest: VWAP made more net over 3yr (+574 vs +469/unit) but bumpier. Toggle to A/B test live.")
vwapArmProfit   = input.float(1.0,  "VWAP Cross — arm after profit ($)", step=0.25, group=grpX)
exitOnClose     = input.bool(false, "Stop exits fill at bar CLOSE (OFF = resting stop, ADOPTED)", group=grpX, tooltip="OFF (default, ADOPTED) = REAL broker resting stop: stop-type exits fill INTRABAR at the stop level, gap-aware. Place OCO stops with your broker. ON = the old alerts-only model (fill on the bar close); use only if you are NOT resting stops.")

grpC = "Entry Confirmation"
confirmBreakout   = input.bool(false, "Require confirmation candle (2-candle break)", group=grpC, tooltip="DEFAULT OFF (Config A): under the resting stop, confirmation is net-negative (the stop already caps whipsaws at $5). ON = enter only after the NEXT candle also closes beyond the trigger (higher win rate but ~-$57/yr net; use with close-fill).")
requireTrendCandle = input.bool(true, "Confirmation candle must be with-trend", group=grpC, tooltip="ON = the confirmation candle must be green for longs / red for shorts.")

grpV = "Reversal"
revQtyMult = input.float(2.0, "Reversal Size Multiplier (before risk cap)", step=0.5, group=grpV)
revRiskCap = input.float(6.0, "Reversal Dollar-Risk Cap ($, 0=off)", step=0.5, group=grpV, tooltip="Risk parity: scale the reversal qty so (entry -> OR boundary) x qty <= this. The primary's average risk is ~$6.16.")

grpU = "Display"
showLabels = input.bool(true, "Show Entry/Exit Labels", group=grpU)
showLevels = input.bool(true, "Show OR / Trigger Levels", group=grpU)
showTable  = input.bool(true, "Show Summary Table", group=grpU)

// ==================== PRIOR-DAY REALISED VOLATILITY (no repaint) ====================
// Safe idiom: lookahead_on + [1] returns the LAST COMPLETED daily value (no future leak).
// Matches Python: daily_close.pct_change().rolling(20).std(ddof=1) * 100, shifted 1 day.
f_priorRvol() =>
    r = ta.change(close) / close[1] * 100.0
    s = ta.stdev(r, volLookback, false)   // biased=false -> sample stdev (pandas ddof=1)
    s[1]
rvol20 = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_priorRvol(), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_on)

// ==================== STATE ====================
var float orHigh = na
var float orLow = na
var float orWidth = na
var bool skipVol = false
var bool skipWide = false
var bool daySkipped = false

var bool firstTaken = false
var bool active = false
var int tdir = 0
var float entry = na
var float stop = na
var float tp = na
var int entryBar = na
var bool inRev = false
var bool suppressPartial = false

var bool beTrig = false
var float beLevel = na
var bool part1 = false
var bool vwapArmed = false
var float qtyTotal = na
var float effQty = na
var float part1Pnl = 0.0
var float runnerPeak = na

var int primDir = 0
var bool primStopped = false

var float dayPnl = 0.0
var bool dayHasTrades = false

// stats
var int nTrades = 0
var int nSucc = 0
var int nFail = 0
var float netPnl = 0.0
var float grossP = 0.0
var float grossL = 0.0
var float worstDay = na
var float bestDay = na
var int totalDays = 0
var int tradeDays = 0
var int volSkipDays = 0
var int wideSkipDays = 0
var int cBEStop = 0
var int cBETrail = 0
var int cBaseSL = 0
var int cTrail = 0
var int cEOD = 0
var int cPart = 0
var int cRev = 0

// alert flags (reset every bar)
aEntryL = false
aEntryS = false
aRevL = false
aRevS = false
aBEFired = false
aPart = false
aTrailX = false
aBEStop = false
aBETrail = false
aBaseSL = false
aEOD = false

// ==================== NEW DAY / OPENING RANGE ====================
isNewDay = session.isfirstbar_regular
sessVwap = ta.vwap(hlc3, isNewDay)   // session-anchored VWAP for the optional VWAP-cross runner exit
isEODbar = (hour * 60 + minute) >= (eodHour * 60 + eodMin)

if isNewDay
    // finalise the previous day before resetting
    if dayHasTrades
        worstDay := na(worstDay) ? dayPnl : math.min(worstDay, dayPnl)
        bestDay := na(bestDay) ? dayPnl : math.max(bestDay, dayPnl)
        tradeDays += 1
    totalDays += 1
    dayPnl := 0.0
    dayHasTrades := false
    orHigh := high
    orLow := low
    orWidth := high - low
    skipVol := not na(rvol20) and rvol20 > maxRvolPct
    skipWide := orWidth > maxORWidth
    daySkipped := skipVol or skipWide
    if skipVol
        volSkipDays += 1
    else if skipWide
        wideSkipDays += 1
    firstTaken := false
    active := false
    tdir := 0
    entry := na
    stop := na
    tp := na
    entryBar := na
    inRev := false
    suppressPartial := false
    beTrig := false
    beLevel := na
    part1 := false
    qtyTotal := na
    effQty := na
    part1Pnl := 0.0
    runnerPeak := na
    primDir := 0
    primStopped := false

longBrk = not na(orHigh) ? orHigh + orWidth * bufferPctOR / 100.0 : na
shortBrk = not na(orLow) ? orLow - orWidth * bufferPctOR / 100.0 : na
tpDist = not na(orWidth) ? math.max(adaptiveTPMin, orWidth * adaptiveTPScale) : na
// No new entries at/after the EOD cutoff (matches the Python engine's entry block); the position
// is force-closed on the EOD bar below. This is time-based (not barstate), so it is safe live.
canTrade = session.ismarket and not isNewDay and not daySkipped and not na(orHigh) and not isEODbar

// Confirmation: require the previous bar to ALSO have closed beyond the trigger (a held 2-candle
// break), and (optionally) a with-trend confirmation candle. Enters on this (the confirming) bar.
longConfirm  = not confirmBreakout or (close[1] > longBrk and (close >= open or not requireTrendCandle))
shortConfirm = not confirmBreakout or (close[1] < shortBrk and (close <= open or not requireTrendCandle))

// ==================== PRIMARY ENTRY ====================
if canTrade and not active and not firstTaken
    if close > longBrk and longConfirm
        active := true
        tdir := 1
        inRev := false
        suppressPartial := false
        entry := close
        stop := maxCapSL > 0 ? math.max(orLow, close - maxCapSL) : orLow
        tp := close + tpDist
        beLevel := orHigh - beTrigger * orWidth
        entryBar := bar_index
        qtyTotal := tradeQty
        effQty := tradeQty
        part1 := false
        part1Pnl := 0.0
        beTrig := false
        runnerPeak := na
        primDir := 1
        firstTaken := true
        aEntryL := true
        if showLabels
            label.new(bar_index, low, "LONG " + str.tostring(entry, format.mintick), style=label.style_label_up, color=color.rgb(7, 170, 75), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
    else if close < shortBrk and shortConfirm
        active := true
        tdir := -1
        inRev := false
        suppressPartial := false
        entry := close
        stop := maxCapSL > 0 ? math.min(orHigh, close + maxCapSL) : orHigh
        tp := close - tpDist
        beLevel := orLow + beTrigger * orWidth
        entryBar := bar_index
        qtyTotal := tradeQty
        effQty := tradeQty
        part1 := false
        part1Pnl := 0.0
        beTrig := false
        runnerPeak := na
        primDir := -1
        firstTaken := true
        aEntryS := true
        if showLabels
            label.new(bar_index, high, "SHORT " + str.tostring(entry, format.mintick), style=label.style_label_down, color=color.rgb(243, 76, 76), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)

// ==================== REVERSAL ENTRY (raw OR break · trail-to-EOD · risk-parity size) ====================
if canTrade and primStopped and not active
    if primDir == 1 and close < orLow
        rpu = math.abs(close - orHigh)
        rq = revRiskCap > 0 and rpu > 0 ? math.min(tradeQty * revQtyMult, revRiskCap / rpu) : tradeQty * revQtyMult
        active := true
        tdir := -1
        inRev := true
        suppressPartial := true
        entry := close
        stop := orHigh
        tp := na
        beLevel := orLow + beTrigger * orWidth
        entryBar := bar_index
        qtyTotal := rq
        effQty := rq
        part1 := false
        part1Pnl := 0.0
        beTrig := false
        runnerPeak := na
        primStopped := false
        cRev += 1
        aRevS := true
        if showLabels
            label.new(bar_index, high, "REV SHORT " + str.tostring(entry, format.mintick) + "\nqty " + str.tostring(rq, "#.##"), style=label.style_label_down, color=color.purple, textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
    else if primDir == -1 and close > orHigh
        rpu = math.abs(close - orLow)
        rq = revRiskCap > 0 and rpu > 0 ? math.min(tradeQty * revQtyMult, revRiskCap / rpu) : tradeQty * revQtyMult
        active := true
        tdir := 1
        inRev := true
        suppressPartial := true
        entry := close
        stop := orLow
        tp := na
        beLevel := orHigh - beTrigger * orWidth
        entryBar := bar_index
        qtyTotal := rq
        effQty := rq
        part1 := false
        part1Pnl := 0.0
        beTrig := false
        runnerPeak := na
        primStopped := false
        cRev += 1
        aRevL := true
        if showLabels
            label.new(bar_index, low, "REV LONG " + str.tostring(entry, format.mintick) + "\nqty " + str.tostring(rq, "#.##"), style=label.style_label_up, color=color.purple, textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)

// ==================== EXIT ENGINE (never fires on the entry bar) ====================
if active and not na(stop) and bar_index > entryBar
    // --- Step 1: BE Retrace (WICK-based trigger, as in the Python engine) ---
    if not beTrig and not na(beLevel)
        beFire = tdir == 1 ? low <= beLevel : high >= beLevel
        if beFire
            stop := tdir == 1 ? math.max(stop, entry) : math.min(stop, entry)
            beTrig := true
            aBEFired := true

    // --- Step 2: BE Trail ---
    if beTrig and beTrailAmt > 0
        stop := tdir == 1 ? math.max(stop, high - beTrailAmt) : math.min(stop, low + beTrailAmt)

    // --- Step 3: Runner exit (primary only, after the partial). Peak-Trail (A) or VWAP-Cross (B). ---
    if not part1
        vwapArmed := false          // not in a runner yet -> resets per trade
    runnerHit = false
    float runnerPx = na
    string runnerReason = "Trail"
    vwapMode = runnerExit == "VWAP Cross"
    if part1 and not suppressPartial and vwapMode
        // Config B: arm once the trade is +$vwapArmProfit, then exit when close crosses back thru VWAP
        if not vwapArmed and (tdir == 1 ? close - entry : entry - close) >= vwapArmProfit
            vwapArmed := true
        if vwapArmed and not na(sessVwap) and (tdir == 1 ? close <= sessVwap : close >= sessVwap)
            runnerHit := true
            runnerPx := close
            runnerReason := "VWAP Cross"
    else if part1 and not suppressPartial and runnerMult > 0
        // Config A: peak-trail (resting stop at runnerMult x OR below the peak)
        if tdir == 1
            runnerPeak := na(runnerPeak) ? high : math.max(runnerPeak, high)
            lvl = runnerPeak - runnerMult * orWidth
            if exitOnClose ? close <= lvl : low <= lvl
                runnerHit := true
                runnerPx := exitOnClose ? close : lvl
        else
            runnerPeak := na(runnerPeak) ? low : math.min(runnerPeak, low)
            lvl = runnerPeak + runnerMult * orWidth
            if exitOnClose ? close >= lvl : high >= lvl
                runnerHit := true
                runnerPx := exitOnClose ? close : lvl

    // --- Step 4: hit checks. Resting stop (exitOnClose OFF): trigger on the WICK, fill at the
    //     stop level, or at the OPEN if the bar gapped through it (gap-aware, matches engine touch).
    slHit = tdir == 1 ? (exitOnClose ? close <= stop : low <= stop) : (exitOnClose ? close >= stop : high >= stop)
    slFill = exitOnClose ? close : (tdir == 1 ? math.min(stop, open) : math.max(stop, open))
    tpHit = not na(tp) and (tdir == 1 ? high >= tp : low <= tp)

    if slHit
        exitPx = slFill
        perUnit = tdir == 1 ? (exitPx - entry - slippage) : (entry - exitPx - slippage)
        pnlTotal = perUnit * effQty + part1Pnl
        isBETrail = beTrig and (tdir == 1 ? exitPx > entry : exitPx < entry)
        reason = beTrig ? (isBETrail ? "BE Trail" : "BE Stop") : "Base SL"
        if isBETrail
            cBETrail += 1
            aBETrail := true
        else if beTrig
            cBEStop += 1
            aBEStop := true
        else
            cBaseSL += 1
            aBaseSL := true
        nTrades += 1
        if pnlTotal > 0
            nSucc += 1
            grossP += pnlTotal
        else
            nFail += 1
            grossL += math.abs(pnlTotal)
        netPnl += pnlTotal
        dayPnl += pnlTotal
        dayHasTrades := true
        if not inRev
            primStopped := true
        if showLabels
            revNote = (not inRev and primStopped) ? "\nREV armed: need close " + (tdir == 1 ? "< " + str.tostring(orLow, format.mintick) : "> " + str.tostring(orHigh, format.mintick)) : ""
            label.new(bar_index, tdir == 1 ? low : high, (inRev ? "REV " : "") + reason + " " + str.tostring(exitPx, format.mintick) + "\n" + (pnlTotal >= 0 ? "+" : "") + str.tostring(pnlTotal, "#.##") + revNote, style=tdir == 1 ? label.style_label_up : label.style_label_down, color=isBETrail ? color.rgb(7, 170, 75) : color.orange, textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
        active := false
        tdir := 0
        inRev := false
        tp := na
        stop := na
    else if tpHit and not suppressPartial and not part1
        // 25% partial AT the TP level (limit fill); the remainder trails
        p1qty = qtyTotal * partialPct / 100.0
        pu = tdir == 1 ? (tp - entry - slippage) : (entry - tp - slippage)
        part1Pnl := pu * p1qty
        effQty := qtyTotal - p1qty
        part1 := true
        cPart += 1
        aPart := true
        if showLabels
            label.new(bar_index, tdir == 1 ? high : low, "PARTIAL " + str.tostring(partialPct, "#") + "% @ " + str.tostring(tp, format.mintick) + "\n+" + str.tostring(part1Pnl, "#.##"), style=tdir == 1 ? label.style_label_down : label.style_label_up, color=color.rgb(7, 170, 75), textcolor=color.white, size=size.tiny)
        tp := na
    else if runnerHit
        exitPx = runnerPx
        perUnit = tdir == 1 ? (exitPx - entry - slippage) : (entry - exitPx - slippage)
        pnlTotal = perUnit * effQty + part1Pnl
        cTrail += 1
        aTrailX := true
        nTrades += 1
        if pnlTotal > 0
            nSucc += 1
            grossP += pnlTotal
        else
            nFail += 1
            grossL += math.abs(pnlTotal)
        netPnl += pnlTotal
        dayPnl += pnlTotal
        dayHasTrades := true
        if showLabels
            label.new(bar_index, tdir == 1 ? high : low, runnerReason + " " + str.tostring(exitPx, format.mintick) + "\n" + (pnlTotal >= 0 ? "+" : "") + str.tostring(pnlTotal, "#.##"), style=tdir == 1 ? label.style_label_down : label.style_label_up, color=color.new(color.aqua, 0), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
        active := false
        tdir := 0
        inRev := false
        tp := na
        stop := na

// ==================== EOD FORCED CLOSE ====================
if active and isEODbar and tdir != 0
    exitPx = close
    perUnit = tdir == 1 ? (exitPx - entry - slippage) : (entry - exitPx - slippage)
    pnlTotal = perUnit * effQty + part1Pnl
    cEOD += 1
    aEOD := true
    nTrades += 1
    if pnlTotal > 0
        nSucc += 1
        grossP += pnlTotal
    else
        nFail += 1
        grossL += math.abs(pnlTotal)
    netPnl += pnlTotal
    dayPnl += pnlTotal
    dayHasTrades := true
    if showLabels
        label.new(bar_index, close, (inRev ? "REV EOD " : "EOD ") + str.tostring(exitPx, format.mintick) + "\n" + (pnlTotal >= 0 ? "+" : "") + str.tostring(pnlTotal, "#.##"), style=label.style_label_left, color=color.rgb(255, 140, 0), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
    active := false
    tdir := 0
    inRev := false
    tp := na
    stop := na

// ==================== VISUALS ====================
plot(showLevels and not daySkipped and not na(orHigh) ? orHigh : na, "OR High", color=color.new(color.aqua, 0), style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(showLevels and not daySkipped and not na(orLow) ? orLow : na, "OR Low", color=color.new(color.aqua, 0), style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(showLevels and not daySkipped and not na(longBrk) ? longBrk : na, "Long Trigger", color=color.new(color.lime, 0), style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(showLevels and not daySkipped and not na(shortBrk) ? shortBrk : na, "Short Trigger", color=color.new(color.red, 0), style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(active ? stop : na, "Active Stop", color=color.red, linewidth=2, style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(active and not na(tp) ? tp : na, "Active TP", color=color.lime, linewidth=2, style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(active and not beTrig and not na(beLevel) ? beLevel : na, "BE Trigger", color=color.new(color.yellow, 0), style=plot.style_circles)
// Reversal trigger: shown only while a reversal is ARMED (primary stopped, none taken yet).
// The reversal is the OPPOSITE direction, so price must CLOSE beyond this raw OR boundary.
revTrigger = primStopped and not active ? (primDir == 1 ? orLow : orHigh) : na
plot(revTrigger, "Reversal Trigger (needs a CLOSE beyond)", color=color.new(color.purple, 0), linewidth=2, style=plot.style_circles)
bgcolor(daySkipped ? color.new(color.gray, 90) : na, title="Day skipped (vol regime / wide OR)")

// ==================== ALERTS ====================
if barstate.isconfirmed
    base = " | " + syminfo.ticker + " " + timeframe.period + "m | Px $" + str.tostring(close, "#.##") + " | " + str.format_time(time, "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm", "America/New_York") + " ET"
    if aEntryL
        alert("[ENTRY] LONG breakout — BUY at market" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aEntryS
        alert("[ENTRY] SHORT breakout — SELL SHORT at market" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aRevL
        alert("[ENTRY-REV] REVERSAL LONG (risk-parity size) — BUY at market" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aRevS
        alert("[ENTRY-REV] REVERSAL SHORT (risk-parity size) — SELL SHORT at market" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aBEFired
        alert("[STATE] BE RETRACE FIRED — move stop to ENTRY" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aPart
        alert("[EXIT-PARTIAL] Partial closed at TP; runner now trails" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aTrailX
        alert("[EXIT-WIN] RUNNER TRAIL — close remaining position" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aBETrail
        alert("[EXIT-WIN] BE TRAIL — close position in profit" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aBEStop
        alert("[EXIT-LOSS] BE STOP — close position (real loss, filled at close)" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aBaseSL
        alert("[EXIT-LOSS] BASE STOP LOSS — close position" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if aEOD
        alert("[EXIT-EOD] End-of-day forced close" + base, alert.freq_once_per_bar)

// ==================== SUMMARY TABLE ====================
var table tbl = table.new(position.top_right, 2, 16, border_width=1)

f_row(_r, _k, _v, _col) =>
    table.cell(tbl, 0, _r, _k, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.rgb(25, 25, 25), text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(tbl, 1, _r, _v, text_color=_col, bgcolor=color.rgb(25, 25, 25), text_size=size.small)

if barstate.islast and showTable
    // fold the still-open final day into best/worst so the table is complete
    wD = dayHasTrades ? (na(worstDay) ? dayPnl : math.min(worstDay, dayPnl)) : worstDay
    bD = dayHasTrades ? (na(bestDay) ? dayPnl : math.max(bestDay, dayPnl)) : bestDay
    tD = tradeDays + (dayHasTrades ? 1 : 0)
    wr = nTrades > 0 ? nSucc * 100.0 / nTrades : 0.0
    pf = grossL > 0 ? grossP / grossL : na
    exp = nTrades > 0 ? netPnl / nTrades : 0.0

    table.cell(tbl, 0, 0, "UDB-ORB v2.0", text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.rgb(50, 30, 10), text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(tbl, 1, 0, "Realistic Fills", text_color=color.orange, bgcolor=color.rgb(50, 30, 10), text_size=size.small)
    f_row(1, "Trades", str.tostring(nTrades), color.yellow)
    f_row(2, "Success / Fail", str.tostring(nSucc) + " / " + str.tostring(nFail), color.silver)
    f_row(3, "Win Rate", str.tostring(wr, "#.#") + "%", color.orange)
    f_row(4, "Net P&L", (netPnl >= 0 ? "+" : "") + str.tostring(netPnl, "#.##"), netPnl >= 0 ? color.lime : color.red)
    f_row(5, "Profit Factor", na(pf) ? "n/a" : str.tostring(pf, "#.##"), na(pf) ? color.silver : (pf >= 1 ? color.lime : color.red))
    f_row(6, "Expectancy", (exp >= 0 ? "+" : "") + str.tostring(exp, "#.###"), exp >= 0 ? color.lime : color.red)
    f_row(7, "Best Day", na(bD) ? "-" : "+" + str.tostring(bD, "#.##"), color.lime)
    f_row(8, "Worst Day", na(wD) ? "-" : str.tostring(wD, "#.##"), color.red)
    f_row(9, "Trade Days", str.tostring(tD) + " / " + str.tostring(totalDays), color.aqua)
    f_row(10, "Skipped: High Vol", str.tostring(volSkipDays), color.fuchsia)
    f_row(11, "Skipped: Wide OR", str.tostring(wideSkipDays), color.fuchsia)
    f_row(12, "Reversals", str.tostring(cRev), color.purple)
    f_row(13, "BE Stop / Trail", str.tostring(cBEStop) + " / " + str.tostring(cTrail), color.silver)
    f_row(14, "EOD / Partials", str.tostring(cEOD) + " / " + str.tostring(cPart), color.silver)
    f_row(15, "Prior RVol", na(rvol20) ? "n/a" : str.tostring(rvol20, "#.##") + "%" + (skipVol ? "  SKIP" : ""), skipVol ? color.red : color.lime)
